	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 24th 3:58 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>well has anyone noticed the sheer fact that us clerics cannot solo for sh*t! every other class can. i do not care what anyone says.  and i do not mean like soloing in the 50's cause that deserves mad props. I have a lvl 13 cleric and we cant solo for a thing, and at the same lvl all other classes can. for example, pally, warrior, sk, rangers, can all solo till about lvl 20. monks do their mad damage, druids can kite until like lvl 55 (i know my friend does it) necros can send their pets(even though they die fast one engulfing darkness and a few dots and it is over), wizard root blast kill, magician-pet, shaman can kite cause they can sow themselves, rogues can run around backstabbin, but clerics get a 25 dmg aoe that takes forever to cast and what else, fear oh yah send it off to run away and pull the rest of the zone or follow it and die even faster. if we had a decent dmg spell at that lvl we could root and kill but the aoe is touch. we have terrible melee skills, we dont even get shield bash, and in unrest for example and average char cant kill any yard trash cause of no mana. the undead dd does 41 at max and if you can cast it 6 times and run out of mana little good will it do you on a 400 hp mob!<br><br>but none the less, at 14 we get our new smite spell and our new undead spell. but i do manage to solo every once in a while but i get the worst exp! and this is from like yellow orc emmisaries in CB! i will get like 1/5 of a blue bub but i know this is good for like a real high lvl i will go to my friends house (he has a warrior same lvl as me) and watch him get like 1/3 of a blue bar off one blue legionare! (please forgive any misspelling that may have occurred)<br><br>Jefro<br>lvl 13 DWF cler<br>tarew marr<br><br>P.S.  I am not usually in such a bad mood but if you see me on then send me a tell.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
