	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>From 13 to 16 go to the Oasis. Setup just to the East of the Ocean right near the North Ro Zone. There is a canyon just as you zone in near the ocean. Fight North of the canyon at the East end of the canyon. There is a flat area just to the north and then a small rise which is the zone edge. If things get hot zone.<br><br>Use your Sense the Dead spell (you did buy this very useful spell right?) to find a mummy or zombie that cons even or blue. You might have to run to find it. I'd pretty much avoid everything that is not undead since you probably can't solo it until 14. Pull the Undead Baddie back to the Zone line by casting Ward or Furor at max range and then running back to your spot by the zone. As a HE I could out run most of the dead stuff even without SOW. Then just Root and Ward Undead until dead again.<br><br>It gets even better once you hit 14 and get Expulse the Dead. Start killing anything Undead that is yellow you can find including Dry Bones and Ghouls. Exp is decent.<br><br>Be sure to buy Cure Disease because Rabies Sucks. In your spare time, you can also make a little extra money curing people in either the Oasis or in North Ro. I always offer my services for free but will not turn down a donation if offered (and people do offer).<br><br>I know I have never used any of my AoE damage spells. I am not sure I even purchased them. Money was tight back then. <br><br>Once you hit 16 or 17 go to Ill Omen and do what you were born to do. Get in groups and heal.<br><br>Andav<br>Madcap Cleric of 30 Seasons<br>Tunare Server<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
